@startuml vectranetworks_AWS-Traffic-Mirroring-Session-Manager
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor Administrator

rectangle "CLI Interface" as CLI {
}

rectangle "tap.py" as Tap #lightblue

rectangle "config_vpc.py" as ConfigVPC #palegreen

rectangle "ec2_api_client.py" as EC2Client #mistyrose

rectangle "spile_tapper.py" as SpileTapper #lightyellow

rectangle "spile.py" as Spile #aliceblue

rectangle "AWS EC2 API" as AWS #lightsteelblue

' ========== Connections ==========
Administrator --> CLI : Runs commands\n(config/blacklist/whitelist/heal)

CLI --> ConfigVPC : configure VPC settings
CLI --> Tap : manage mirroring sessions

Tap --> SpileTapper : iterate VPCs\nmanage sessions
SpileTapper --> Spile : create/remove sessions\nper ENI
SpileTapper --> EC2Client : discover instances\nmanage tags

Spile --> EC2Client : create/delete\nmirror sessions
EC2Client --> AWS : API calls\n(tags, instances, sessions)

ConfigVPC --> EC2Client : store config\nin tags
@enduml